# 全銀協 Zengin Format Specification

Invoke `@zengin-spec` for authoritative byte layouts, field definitions,
and encoding rules for Zengin format files.

## Overview

全銀協標準通信プロトコル (Zengin) is the standard format for Japanese bank
transfer files. Files consist of fixed-length 120-byte records in Shift_JIS.

## File Structure

```
[Header Record]     1 record  (record type = 1)
[Data Records]      N records (record type = 2)
[Trailer Record]    1 record  (record type = 8)
[End Record]        1 record  (record type = 9)
```

## Header Record (120 bytes)

| Pos | Len | Field | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | 1 | レコード区分 | `'1'` |
| 2 | 2 | 種別コード | `'11'`=給与, `'12'`=賞与 |
| 4 | 1 | コード区分 | `'0'`=JIS, `'1'`=EBCDIC |
| 5 | 10 | 委託者コード | |
| 15 | 40 | 委託者名 | half-width kana |
| 55 | 4 | 取組日 | MMDD (月日) |
| 59 | 4 | 仕向銀行番号 | source bank code |
| 63 | 15 | 仕向銀行名 | half-width kana |
| 78 | 3 | 仕向支店番号 | source branch code |
| 81 | 15 | 仕向支店名 | half-width kana |
| 96 | 1 | 預金種別 | `'1'`=普通, `'2'`=当座 |
| 97 | 7 | 口座番号 | right-justified, zero-padded |
| 104 | 17 | ダミー | spaces |

## Data Record (120 bytes)

| Pos | Len | Field | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | 1 | レコード区分 | `'2'` |
| 2 | 4 | 被仕向銀行番号 | destination bank code |
| 6 | 15 | 被仕向銀行名 | half-width kana |
| 21 | 3 | 被仕向支店番号 | destination branch code |
| 24 | 15 | 被仕向支店名 | half-width kana |
| 39 | 4 | ダミー | spaces |
| 43 | 1 | 預金種別 | `'1'`=普通, `'2'`=当座, `'4'`=貯蓄 |
| 44 | 7 | 口座番号 | right-justified, zero-padded |
| 51 | 30 | 受取人名 | half-width kana |
| 81 | 10 | 振込金額 | right-justified, zero-padded |
| 91 | 1 | 新規コード | `'1'`=初回, `'2'`=変更, `'0'`=その他 |
| 92 | 20 | EDI情報 | optional, space-padded |
| 112 | 1 | 振込区分 | `'7'`=電信, `'9'`=文書 |
| 113 | 8 | ダミー | spaces |

## Trailer Record (120 bytes)

| Pos | Len | Field | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | 1 | レコード区分 | `'8'` |
| 2 | 6 | 合計件数 | right-justified, zero-padded |
| 8 | 12 | 合計金額 | right-justified, zero-padded |
| 20 | 101 | ダミー | spaces |

## End Record

Single record, all spaces except position 1 = `'9'`.

## Half-Width Kana Rules

- Use half-width katakana only (半角カナ, JIS X 0201)
- Voiced consonants: ガ → ｶﾞ (occupies 2 bytes)
- Semi-voiced: パ → ﾊﾟ (occupies 2 bytes)
- Full-width characters must be converted before measuring field length
- If converted text exceeds field byte length, throw an error (never truncate)

## Encoding

- Shift_JIS (CP932) for the entire file
- Numeric fields: ASCII digits, right-justified, zero-padded
- Text fields: half-width kana + ASCII, left-justified, space-padded
